## 2. Copyleft Requirement

Any modified version, derivative work, or redistribution — whether in source or binary form —  
**must also be licensed under the Qyzyl License**.  
This ensures that all versions of this software remain free and open forever.

You may not relicense, sublicense, or combine this code into a project  
that uses a different or more restrictive license.

---

## 3. Source Code Availability

If you distribute binaries, modified versions, or derivative works of this software,  
you **must make the complete and corresponding source code**  
available to the public in an easily accessible form  
(e.g., via a public Git repository or downloadable archive).  

Private, non-public distributions are permitted for testing or internal use  
only if no third-party users are affected.

---

## 4. Modification and Publication

You may freely modify, adapt, or extend this software.  
You may publish or distribute modified versions,  
provided that you retain:

- the original copyright notice,  
- the full text of this license,  
- and clear documentation of the changes you made.

Attribution must state:

> “Based on Qyzyl Software Distribution © The Qyzyl Project.”

